{{Infobox power station|name=Kilgallioch Wind Farm|name_official=|image=|image_size=|image_caption=Kilgallioch Wind Farm|image_alt=|location_map=UK Scotland|relief=1|location_map_size=|location_map_caption=Location of Kilgallioch Wind Farm in Scotland|coordinates={{coord|55|03|00|N|04|45|55|W|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline,title}}|coordinates_ref=|country=Scotland, United Kingdom|location=[[South Ayrshire]]|status=Operational|construction_began=2015|commissioned=|decommissioned=|cost=|owner=[[ScottishPower Renewables]]|operator=[[Scottish Power]]|ps_units_operational=96 X 2.5&nbsp;MW|ps_units_manu_model=[[Gamesa Corporación Tecnológica|Gamesa]]: G90 and G114|wind_hub_height=|wind_rotor_diameter=|wind_rated_speed=|wind_farm_type=Onshore|wind_site_elevation=|wind_site_usage=|wind_site_area=|ps_electrical_capacity=239 [[Megawatt|MW]]|ps_electrical_cap_fac=|website=|extra=}}
'''Kilgallioch Wind Farm''' is a 96 turbine [[wind farm]] in [[South Ayrshire]], [[Scotland]] with a total capacity of up to 239 [[megawatts]] (MW). <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scottishpowerrenewables.com/pages/kilgallioch.aspx|title=Kilgallioch Windfarm - ScottishPower Renewables|website=www.scottishpowerrenewables.com|language=en|access-date=2017-03-18}}</ref> Consent granted by the Scottish Government in February 2013 with construction starting in 2015 and completed in 2017.

== Incidents ==
On 13 January 2017 a turbine under construction catastrophically collapsed during a storm.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/local-news/safety-probe-launched-after-collapse-9716684|title=Panic as giant 480ft wind turbine collapses|last=Houston|first=Stephen|date=2017-01-29|work=dailyrecord|access-date=2017-03-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-south-scotland-38689763|title=Kilgallioch wind farm turbine incident under investigation|date=2017-01-20|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-03-18|language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 15 March 2017 Portuguese construction worker António João Linares, who was working for turbine manufacturer Gamesa, was killed when he fell 8 metres within a tower.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cmjornal.pt/portugal/detalhe/portugues-morre-em-queda-de-150-metros-na-escocia|title=Português morre em queda de 150 metros na Escócia|access-date=2017-03-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thescottishsun.co.uk/news/732023/man-falls-from-wind-turbine-kilgallioch-wind-farm/|title=Man, 37, plummets to his death while working at 480ft wind turbine farm|date=2017-03-16|work=The Scottish Sun|access-date=2017-03-18|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-south-scotland-39294942|title=Worker dies in Kilgallioch wind farm accident|date=2017-03-16|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-03-18|language=en-GB}}</ref>

