{{Infobox film | name = Lady Urmia | image = | alt = <!-- see WP:ALT --> | caption = | director = Mohammad Ehsani | producer = [[Mohammad Ala]] | writer = | screenplay = | story = | starring = | music = | cinematography = | editing = Mastaneh Mohajer | studio = | distributor = Mohammad Ehsani (EhsaniPictures) | released = 2012 | runtime = 30 minutes | country = [[Iran]] | language = Persian | budget = | gross = }}
'''Lady Urmia''' ({{lang-fa|بانوی ارومیه}}) is an [[Iranian languages|Iranian]] [[documentary film]] by Mohammad Ehsani.<ref name="realp">{{cite web|url=http://www.reelport.com/index.php?id=300&L=de%2525252525252525252525252527&movie_id=53861&last_page=catalogue.results.all|title=Details - Banooye Urmia|accessdate=25 December 2012}}</ref> It was released in 2012 in [[Iran]], distributed by EhsaniPictures.<ref name=realp />
==Synopsis== The film is a [[poetic]] documentary about [[Lake Urmia]], in [[Azerbaijan (Iran)|Iranian Azerbaijan]], which is drying up completely. The environmental catastrophe will not only affect Iran, but also neighbors such as [[Iraq]] and [[Turkey]]. The film is narrated in the voice of the Lake itself, asking for help and trying to gain international reaction.
