The '''Self-Protect High-Energy Laser Demonstrator''' ('''SHiELD''') is a [[directed energy weapon]]s development program.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.flightglobal.com/news/articles/usaf-considers-defensive-lasers-for-future-fighters-421535/|title=USAF considers defensive lasers for future fighters|date=2 February 2016|website=flightglobal.com|accessdate=11 November 2017}}</ref><ref>http://www.janes.com/article/63185/northrop-grumman-to-develop-laser-pod-to-protect-usaf-fighters</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realcleardefense.com/2016/11/18/the_air_force039s_self-protect_high-energy_laser_demonstrator_287746.html|title=The Air Force's Self-Protect High-Energy Laser Demonstrator - RealClearDefense|website=realcleardefense.com|accessdate=11 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://breakingdefense.com/2015/08/air-force-moves-aggressively-on-lasers/ |title=Air Force Moves Aggressively On Lasers « Breaking Defense - Defense industry news, analysis and commentary |website=Breakingdefense.com |date=2015-08-07 |accessdate=2016-02-17}}</ref> The objective of this programme is to demonstrate the ability of a laser system mounted on aircraft. The program will develop and integrate a moderate power laser in a fighter-compatible pod.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationaldefensemagazine.org/archive/2015/November/Pages/AirForceResearchLabTriestoStayAheadofRivals.aspx |title=Air Force Research Lab Tries to Stay Ahead of Rivals |website=Nationaldefensemagazine.org |date=2011-03-17 |accessdate=2016-02-17}}</ref> It was reported that [[United States Air Force]] is considering to get defensive laser weapon for fifth and sixth generation [[fighter jet]]s by 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defenseindustrydaily.com/usaf-to-become-the-agents-of-shield-pentagon-multi-billion-investment-in-tomahawks-and-sm-6-uk-mod-buying-zephyr-solar-planes-032678/?|title=USAF Become Agents of SHiELD &#124; Pentagon: Multi-Billion Investment Tomahawks SM-6 &#124; UK MoD Buying Zephyr Solar Planes |website=Defenseindustrydaily.com |date=2016-02-05 |accessdate=2016-02-17}}</ref>

