{{Infobox power station | name = Xitieshan Solar Park | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = China | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|37|18|34|N|95|29|05|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = [[China]] | location = [[Qinghai Province]] | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = 30 September 2011 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = CGN | operator = | solar_type = PV | solar_csp_heliostats = | solar_site_area = | ps_electrical_capacity = 100 [[Megawatt|MW<sub>P</sub>]] | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | ps_annual_generation = 164 [[GWh]] | website = | extra = }} CGN's '''Xitieshan Solar Park''' is a 100 [[megawatt]] (MW) [[photovoltaic power station]] located in the [[Qinghai Province]], [[China]]. Construction was completed in three phases, Xitieshan Phase I was 10 MW,<ref>[http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/DB/RINA1328524218.35/view CGN Qinghai Xitieshan Phase I 10MW Grid-connected Solar PV Power Generation Project]</ref> Xitieshan Phase II was 30 MW,<ref>[http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/DB/RINA1332866656.58/view CGN Qinghai Xitieshan Phase II 30MWp Grid-connected Solar PV Power Generation Project]</ref> and Xitieshan Phase III was 60 MW.<ref>[http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/Validation/DB/RKG1K9QEQJFP2VKRP02DWIOS8FP0SL/view.html Xitieshan Phase III 60MWp Grid-connected Solar PV Power Generation Project]</ref> It was completed on 30 September 2011, and at the time was the largest grid connected photovoltaic power station in the world.<ref>[http://www.cgnpc.com.cn/n2881959/n3065920/n3069980/5134988.html 中广核集团青海锡铁山100兆瓦光伏并网发电项目竣工投产] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130121092417/http://www.cgnpc.com.cn/n2881959/n3065920/n3069980/5134988.html |date=January 21, 2013 }} (Chinese)</ref>
